# Yaroslavka, Republic of Bashkortostan

}}
Yaroslavka () is a rural locality (a selo) and the administrative centre of Yaroslavsky Selsoviet, Duvansky District, Bashkortostan, Russia. The population was 2,301 as of 2010. There are twenty streets.
Geography
Yaroslavka is located 50 km northwest of Mesyagutovo (the district's administrative centre) by road. Voznesenka is the nearest rural locality.
